<h2>Manage standards</h2>

<p>DDT Standards help ensure consistency and quality across digital services. To manage standards:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Click on <strong>Standards</strong> in the top navigation menu</li>
    <li>Select <strong>Manage standards</strong> to view all standards</li>
    <li>From here you can:
        <ul>
            <li>View existing standards</li>
            <li>Create new standards</li>
            <li>Edit existing standards</li>
            <li>View published standards</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>Creating a standard</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Click <strong>Create standard</strong> from the Standards menu</li>
    <li>Fill in the standard details:
        <ul>
            <li>Title and description</li>
            <li>Category and tags</li>
            <li>Content and requirements</li>
            <li>Related standards or guidance</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Save as draft or submit for approval</li>
</ol>

<h3>Standard workflow</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Draft</strong> - Standard is being created or edited</li>
    <li><strong>Submitted</strong> - Standard is submitted for review</li>
    <li><strong>Published</strong> - Standard is approved and available to all users</li>
</ul>

<p>Only published standards are visible to all users. Draft and submitted standards are only visible to their creators and administrators.</p>

